description.narrative: By 2023, national and sub national authorities have the knowledge, tools, resources and authority they need to formulate and implement the institutional and legal frameworks to strengthen child protection prevention and response interventions in a more enabling legislative, policy and financing environment., which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Children With Disabilities, Evaluation And Research, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, girls and boys including adolescents, living with families and outside of family care are increasingly free from violence and exploitation and from the threat of violence and exploitation in their homes, schools and communities and in institutions, including during humanitarian situations.

description.narrative: Legislative and policy environment to protect children in Cambodia was further strengthened as the process to develop a Child Protection Law started and the guidelines on diversion of children in conflict with the law and on child-friendly justice procedures were finalized (awaiting Ministry of Justice approval). In order to respond to the child protection impacts of COVID-19, support was provided to update the Child Protection in Emergency Plan and implement key interventions to support continuity of child protection services and prevent and respond to additional risks for children due to COVID19. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:21/08/2020
